      <body>
         <!-- please fill out the template below, replacing text in square brackets with the actual information -->
         <head>
            <title>Witness Statement Provided by Mrs. Faith MacLean</title> 
            <date when-iso="1922-02-09">2-9-22</date>
            <orgName>[Police]</orgName>
         </head>
         <div>
            <byline><persName ref="#wnek">Christine</persName></byline><!-- make sure to add your unique identifier from the header, by adding the @ref attribute in the byline element -->
            
            <!-- Paste your transcription into the structure below, repeating the pattern for each question and answer. -->
            <sp select="question">
               <speaker><persName ref="#police"></persName>POLICE</speaker>
               <ab>When did you first learn that <persName ref="#taylor_william">Mr. Taylor</persName> was dead?</ab> 
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker><persName ref="#maclean">Faith MacLean</persName></speaker>
               <ab><time when-iso="07:30">7:30</time><date>Thursday morning</date>.</ab> 
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="question">
               <speaker><persName ref="#police"></persName>POLICE</speaker>
               <ab>Who was it that brought it to your attention?</ab> 
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker><persName ref="#maclean">Faith MacLean</persName></speaker>
               <ab>His colored servant came screaming out of the house.</ab> 
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="question">
               <speaker><persName ref="#police"></persName>POLICE</speaker>
               <ab>What did he say?</ab> 
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker><persName ref="#maclean">Faith MacLean</persName></speaker>
               <ab>"Help, Police, <persName ref="#taylor_william">Mr. Taylor</persName> is dead."</ab> 
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="question">
               <speaker><persName ref="#police"></persName>POLICE</speaker>
               <ab>Did the fact that <persName ref="#taylor_william">Mr. Taylor</persName> was dead remind you of anything that occurred <date when-iso="1922-02-01">the night before</date> *  did you hear a shot.</ab> 
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker><persName ref="#maclean">Faith MacLean</persName></speaker>
               <ab>Yes, what we thought might be a <objectName type="weapon">shot</objectName> or a muffler explosion, I do not know which.</ab> 
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="question">
               <speaker><persName ref="#police"></persName>POLICE</speaker>
               <ab>When did you hear that?</ab> 
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker><persName ref="#maclean">Faith MacLean</persName></speaker>
               <ab>Sometime probably <time when-iso="19:45-20:00">between quarter of eight and eight o'clock</time> on <date>Wednesday evening</date>.</ab> 
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="question">
               <speaker><persName ref="#police"></persName>POLICE</speaker>
               <ab>Now, at the time you heard this <objectName type="weapon">shot</objectName> did you go out on the <objectName type="miscellaneous">porch</objectName></ab> 
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker><persName ref="#maclean">Faith MacLean</persName></speaker>
               <ab>Yes, shortly after *** oh, about, I suppose three or four seconds, maybe a minute.</ab> 
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker><persName ref="#maclean">Faith MacLean</persName></speaker>
               <ab>No I did not I just opened my front <objectName type="miscellaneous">door</objectName>.</ab> 
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="question">
               <speaker><persName ref="#police"></persName>POLICE</speaker>
               <ab>Well, what did you say?</ab> 
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker><persName ref="#maclean">Faith MacLean</persName></speaker>
               <ab>I saw e man had already opened the <objectName type="miscellaneous">door</objectName> of <persName ref="#taylor_william">Mr. Taylor</persName>'s <objectName type="miscellaneous">house</objectName> and was looking towards <placeName ref="#alvarado">Alverado St.</placeName> *** I didn't see him open the <objectName type="miscellaneous">door</objectName>; it was already open I think.</ab> 
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="question">
               <speaker><persName ref="#police"></persName>POLICE</speaker>
               <ab>Which way was the screen?</ab> 
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker><persName ref="#maclean">Faith MacLean</persName></speaker>
               <ab>The screen <objectName type="miscellaneous">door</objectName> was open. I think the screen <objectName type="miscellaneous">door</objectName> was open then I must have been to have seen his figure as clearly as I did.</ab> 
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="question">
               <speaker><persName ref="#police"></persName>POLICE</speaker>
               <ab>Did he shut the <objectName type="miscellaneous">door</objectName>?</ab> 
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker><persName ref="#maclean">Faith MacLean</persName></speaker>
               <ab>It seems like he shut the <objectName type="miscellaneous">door</objectName>. It seems like he leaned in and pulled it closed. So it must have been opened because I distinctly saw his <objectName type="clothing">cap</objectName>.</ab> 
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="question">
               <speaker><persName ref="#police"></persName>POLICE</speaker>
               <ab>You are satisfied are you, that the light came from <persName ref="#taylor_william">Taylor's</persName> apartment out on the street through the open door?</ab> 
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker><persName ref="#maclean">Faith MacLean</persName></speaker>
               <ab>Yes.</ab> 
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="question">
               <speaker><persName ref="#police"></persName>POLICE</speaker>
               <ab>Did he seem in a hurry?</ab> 
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker><persName ref="#maclean">Faith MacLean</persName></speaker>
               <ab>No, he was the coolest thing I have ever seen * * *. He turned around and looked at me and hesitated. Then it seems as if * * * that <persName ref="#taylor_william">Mr. Taylor</persName> must have spoken to him from inside the house *** he thought he had spoken and he didn't. Seemed like he pulled the <objectName type="miscellaneous">door</objectName> shut, then turned around and looking at me all the time, walked down a couple ot steps that go up to <persName ref="#taylor_william">Mr. Taylor's</persName> house there.</ab> 
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="question">
               <speaker><persName ref="#police"></persName>POLICE</speaker>
               <ab>Do you know whether the man that you saw went to <placeName ref="#alvarado">Alvarado St.</placeName> through the open court there?</ab> 
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker><persName ref="#maclean">Faith MacLean</persName></speaker>
               <ab>He went towards <placeName ref="#maryland">Maryland St.</placeName> and towards the alley in between the two houses because he was facing that way ready to go when I closed the <objectName type="miscellaneous">door</objectName>.</ab> 
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="question">
               <speaker><persName ref="#police"></persName>POLICE</speaker>
               <ab>You knew it wasn't <persName ref="#taylor_william">Taylor</persName>.</ab> 
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker><persName ref="#maclean">Faith MacLean</persName></speaker>
               <ab>Oh, I knew it wasn't <persName ref="#taylor_william">Taylor</persName>.</ab> 
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="question">
               <speaker><persName ref="#police"></persName>POLICE</speaker>
               <ab>Could you have recognized the man 1f it had been <persName ref="#taylor_william">Mr. Taylor</persName>.</ab> 
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker><persName ref="#maclean">Faith MacLean</persName></speaker>
               <ab>Oh, yes, positively.</ab> 
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="question">
               <speaker><persName ref="#police"></persName>POLICE</speaker>
               <ab>Now, is it possible that it might have been this young man <persName ref="#fellows_howard">Howard Fellows</persName>, the chauffeur, that you saw there. Could that be possible.</ab> 
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker><persName ref="#maclean">Faith MacLean</persName></speaker>
               <ab>I suppose it could be possible but it doesn't seem to me that he was the boy or was the man. He doesn't seem the built of that man.</ab> 
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="question">
               <speaker><persName ref="#police"></persName>POLICE</speaker>
               <ab>Did the man you saw have a <objectName type="body_part">smooth face</objectName>?</ab> 
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker><persName ref="#maclean">Faith MacLean</persName></speaker>
               <ab>Yes, he did have a <objectName type="body_part">smooth face</objectName>.</ab> 
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="question">
               <speaker><persName ref="#police"></persName>POLICE</speaker>
               <ab>Did the man you saw have on anything like a chauffeur's uniform?</ab> 
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker><persName ref="#maclean">Faith MacLean</persName></speaker>
               <ab>Well, the only thing I noticed was his <objectName type="clothing">cap</objectName>, something tied around his <objectName type="body_part">throat</objectName>. I don't know whether the man had an <objectName type="clothing">over-coat</objectName> or not.</ab> 
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker><persName ref="#maclean">Faith MacLean</persName></speaker>
               <ab>His age I don't know but I should judge the man was probably between 30 and 35. He was about 5 feet nine, just about ***, and he was stocky, not fat, but stocky. He had on a <objectName type="clothing">cap</objectName>. It seemed like a checked <objectName type="clothing">cap</objectName> with a plaid in it, and he wore something around his <objectName type="body_part">throat</objectName>.</ab> 
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="question">
               <speaker><persName ref="#police"></persName>POLICE</speaker>
               <ab><objectName type="body_part">Smooth shaven</objectName>?</ab> 
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker><persName ref="#maclean">Faith MacLean</persName></speaker>
               <ab>Yes.</ab> 
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="question">
               <speaker><persName ref="#police"></persName>POLICE</speaker>
               <ab>Color of his <objectName type="clothing">suit</objectName>?</ab> 
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker><persName ref="#maclean">Faith MacLean</persName></speaker>
               <ab>No, except it was a dark <objectName type="clothing">suit</objectName>.</ab> 
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="question">
               <speaker><persName ref="#police"></persName>POLICE</speaker>
               <ab>Now didn't compare in size with <persName ref="#smith">Mr. Smith</persName>, the reporter here, who is taking this statement? (<persName ref="#smith">Mr. Smith</persName> was about 5' 7 1/2")</ab> 
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker><persName ref="#maclean">Faith MacLean</persName></speaker>
               <ab>No, <persName ref="#smith">Mr. Smith</persName> is shorter.</ab> 
            </sp>
            
            <sp>
               <speaker><persName ref="#narrator"></persName>NARRATOR</speaker>
               <ab>(The witness names the following men: <persName ref="#king_henry">Mr. Henry King</persName>, <persName ref="#hamilton_mahlon">Mr. Mahlon Hamilton</persName>, <persName ref="#hoyt_arthur">Mr. Arthur Hoyt</persName>, <persName ref="#berris_nigle">Mr. Berris (first name Nigle?)</persName>, <persName ref="#ince">Mr. Ince</persName>, <persName ref="#neilan_marshal">Mr. Marshal Neilan</persName>. Witness was then asked the following questions)</ab> 
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="question">
               <speaker><persName ref="#police"></persName>POLICE</speaker>
               <ab>Now then, tell me whether there is any possibility that this man you saw coming out of there was any of the persons that you have mentioned?</ab> 
            </sp>
            
            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker><persName ref="#maclean">Faith MacLean</persName></speaker>
               <ab>No, I think not. I think I would have recognized any of those people.</ab> 
               <ab>** when he came out he was dressed as my idea of a moving picture burglar**? ** because I remember thinking perhaps he might have been one of the boys in <persName ref="#taylor_william">Mr. Taylor's</persName> company when they go out on location. Not well dressed. I don't know as I would say slovenly but I don't think he was well dressed.</ab> 
            </sp>
